              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of ἐκδαπανάω ‘to spend completely,’ not occurring in the NT) to do anything and everything to the limit of one’s capacity</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to give oneself completely for</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to do anything and everything</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>If one wishes to preserve something of the underlying figurative meaning of this part of {S:04701201500012}, one may translate ‘I will gladly spend everything and be completely spent on your behalf.’</Comments>
